reviewText: The rating is for the value along with the excellent picture and sound quality. You like these films or you don't, that is up to you. But if you love them like I do, these editions are the best way to get them. They save shelf space and if you shop around you will find even better deals then seen here. The best buy(hint) I found was these two films along with the other double pack with "Dirty Harry" and "Magnum Force" for $20. That's only $5 per blu ray. They aren't stripped of their special features either. So you miss nothing. Collecting doesn't come any cheaper.

reviewText: What a great improvement over what was released within this ' 35 years, 35 films ' offering.  Without going into unnecessary plot summaries, the video transfers for both films was massively improved over the standard definition releases on that collection.  The colors were true and bright and the darks and shadow areas were considerably cleaner.  I won't say that you get the incredible contrast of new films but Warner Brothers did a pretty good job here for these pretty old films.  The films hold up very well and do not seem dated other than hairstyles and cars.  The audio for both films spreads the score of the soundtrack nicely across the front sides but there is little use of the rear surrounds; some but not much.Both movies are on their own separate DVDs in the case which makes assessing them easy.  The extras on both focus on Eastwoods origins in film and his development as both an actor and director. There is some patronizing in the many interviews but the extras remain interesting never the less.For the price, if you are a Dirty Harry fan, these, the 3rd and 4th of the Dirty Harry series, are a great buy on Blu RayAll my movie reviews are of this nature and focus only on the quality of the transfer to BluRay so check them and see if they are of help as well.Hopefully, this review has been of some help to you in determining your purchase, hope I am on the correct path with a review of the transfer quality as opposed to providing plot summaries.Thanks

reviewText: The Enforcer / Sudden Impact (Double Feature) [Blu-ray]Two great Clint Eastwood movies. With Eastwood playing San Fransisco's Inspector Callahan AKA Dirty Harry and all for $9.99. Can't beat that with a wet Inspector Callahan. And it's fun to see all those now vintage autos that we drove way back then. Seams just like yesterday. If your a Clint Eastwood fan I would highly recommend this double Blu-ray DVD. A second in a series of Dirty Harry double Blu-rays.
